		</style>
	</head>
	<body>
		<!--CONTENT_START-->
		<div id="id_content">
			<div class="h1"><a id="df3bea22ca1bd001772585b8368e7dcd"></a>Canon Generic FAX Driver Version 10.57 for Microsoft Windows</div>
			<div class="text">Before using this software, please be sure to read the CANON SOFTWARE LICENSE AGREEMENT displayed during installation. You can also view the CANON SOFTWARE LICENSE AGREEMENT (EULAen-US.rtf) stored in the [misc] in the accompanying CD-ROM or downloaded driver folder.</div>
			<div class="text">This README file contains supplemental information to help you install and use your fax driver software with Microsoft Windows.</div>
			<div class="text">As with most software and hardware products, some information is made available after the development of the manual. Updated information regarding this driver software is provided in this README file. If you require additional assistance, please contact your local Canon company.</div>
			<div class="text">All brand names and product names appearing on this document are registered trademarks or trademarks of their respective owners.</div>
			<div class="text">All other trademarks are the property of their respective owners.</div>
			<div class="h2"><a id="354a09d9c1248a49c2e1db8eea02b0bf"></a>CONTENTS</div>
			<div class="text"><a href="#cf3d925ae8750e1ad7421407ec488b62">Overview</a></div>
			<div class="text"><a href="#1d73139fd5cfcede5cb89645ead72b71">System Requirements</a></div>
			<div class="text"><a href="#9b5bcd3fbd2009731ce32e5dc05fadcd">Installing the Driver</a></div>
			<div class="text"><a href="#716910206d9c7d4ed92497f650b2e755">Configuring Fax Transmission Settings from the Driver</a></div>
			<div class="text"><a href="#809221e1bde0f6449fb73a9ada3b2cf9">Referring to the Help</a></div>
			<div class="text"><a href="#3dc11d3caca53528014c44333c457faa">Available Number of Destinations</a></div>
			<div class="text"><a href="#70e4d832386bc9d8389ca15bbf0f3729">Cautions, Limitations and Restrictions When Installing</a></div>
			<div class="text"><a href="#01c23a0d46d9aa6863ccd11d44e13ced">Cautions, Limitations and Restrictions When Fax Sending</a></div>
			<div class="text"><a href="#6a6da8c9f409ef3310e7d2cc63819c3c">Restrictions Regarding Device Settings</a></div>
			<div class="h2"><a id="cf3d925ae8750e1ad7421407ec488b62"></a>Overview</div>
			<div class="text">This fax driver allows you to send a fax from any Windows application to a remote fax machine if your machine contains an optional fax board.</div>
			<div class="h2"><a id="1d73139fd5cfcede5cb89645ead72b71"></a>System Requirements</div>
			<div class="text">This driver can be used with the following system environments.</div>
			<div class="h5"><a id="73d3cb84ad833e71a3775a70a480f516"></a>Operating System Software</div>
			<div class="text">Microsoft Windows 10/11</div>
			<div class="text">Microsoft Windows Server 2012/2012 R2/2016/2019/2022</div>
			<div class="h5"><a id="79e2836d6ff99846a23e1c4bc9c94b96"></a>With Server-Based Computing Environment</div>
			<div class="h6"><a id="2a59f3f591febb2ec6bf618fe8bd0582"></a>Compatible Windows Terminal Server (Service)</div>
			<div class="text">Microsoft Windows Server 2012/2012 R2/2016/2019/2022</div>
			<div class="h6"><a id="91ed58530d71c10ed72be590e0757886"></a>Compatible Software</div>
			<div class="text">Citrix Virtual Apps and Desktops 7 1912(LTSR)/2109/2112/2203(LTSR)/2206</div>
			<div class="text">VMware vSphere 6.7/7.0</div>
			<div class="text">Microsoft Application Virtualization (App-V)</div>
			<div class="text">Remote Desktop Service on Windows Server 2012 R2/2016/2019/2022</div>
			<div class="h6"><a id="05346a94c9b581ec5083cd9e37baacd7"></a>Operating systems for a clustering server</div>
			<div class="text">Microsoft Windows Server 2012/2012 R2/2016/2019/2022</div>
			<div class="h5"><a id="b645da8b6d74c65ddfca16a856bbe76e"></a>Computer</div>
			<div class="text">Any computer which runs the above operating system software properly.</div>
			<div class="text">However, the ARM architecture is not supported.</div>
			<div class="h2"><a id="9b5bcd3fbd2009731ce32e5dc05fadcd"></a>Installing the Driver</div>
			<div class="text">We recommend that you use the installer to update or add a driver. You can also update or add a driver from the Add Printer Wizard of Windows.</div>
			<div class="text">For details about the installation procedure, refer to the installation guide from the Canon portal site (https://oip.manual.canon/).</div>
			<div class="text">For cautions concerning installation, refer to &quot;<a href="#70e4d832386bc9d8389ca15bbf0f3729">Cautions, Limitations and Restrictions When Installing</a>.&quot;</div>
			<div class="h2"><a id="716910206d9c7d4ed92497f650b2e755"></a>Configuring Fax Transmission Settings from the Driver</div>
			<div class="text">To configure the fax transmission settings using the driver, follow the procedure below.</div>
			<div class="h3"><a id="8053cd3072a73ec8cd11298bb25fc59f"></a>To Change the Default Settings</div>
			<div class="text">Display the fax transmission settings screen and configure the default settings of the driver by following one of the procedures below.</div>
			<div class="text"><span class="bold">If displaying from [Settings] in the Start menu</span></div>
			<div class="text_level1">1. Display [Bluetooth &amp; devices] (or [Devices]).</div>
			<div class="text_level1">2. In [Printers &amp; scanners], display the management screen for the device to set.</div>
			<div class="text_level2">To display the management screen, click the device or click [Manage] for the corresponding device.</div>
			<div class="text_level1">3. Click [Printing preferences] for the device to set.</div>
			<div class="text"><span class="bold">If displaying from the [Control Panel] of Windows</span></div>
			<div class="text_level1">1. Display [Devices and Printers].</div>
			<div class="text_level2">If the [Settings] screen is displayed, refer to the above procedure for displaying the screen from [Settings].</div>
			<div class="text_level1">2. From the printer list, right-click the device to be set → select [Printing preferences] from the displayed menu.</div>
			<div class="h3"><a id="569dbc4c5e0ded43af67ad8cf81e2c42"></a>To Set When Fax Sending</div>
			<div class="text">1. Select the print menu of the application.</div>
			<div class="text">2. In the displayed print screen, select the device you are using → click [Preferences].</div>
			<div class="text_level1">Depending on the application, [Preferences] may be called &quot;Printer properties&quot; or &quot;Properties.&quot;</div>
			<div class="h2"><a id="809221e1bde0f6449fb73a9ada3b2cf9"></a>Referring to the Help</div>
			<div class="text">In order to better understand the usage of online manuals, CANON INC. uses web analysis tools provided by Google Analytics. No personally identifying information about our customers is acquired through the use of Google Analytics. See the following for details.</div>
			<div class="text_level1">http://www.google.com/policies/privacy/partners/</div>
			<div class="text">For information about preventing the use of data by Google Analytics, see the following.</div>
			<div class="text_level1">https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout</div>
			<div class="h2"><a id="3dc11d3caca53528014c44333c457faa"></a>Available Number of Destinations</div>
			<div class="text">The number of destinations you are able to send to at one time varies according to the following settings.</div>
			<div class="h6"><a id="fbd3e45f9e760453472a27e39353e4ad"></a>(1) When [Set the number of destinations that can be specified at once to 2000] is selected:</div>
			<div class="list">If [Cover Sheet Attachment] is [None]: 2000</div>
			<div class="list">If [Cover Sheet Attachment] is [Different Sheet to Each Destination]: 100</div>
			<div class="list">If [Cover Sheet Attachment] is [Same Sheet to All Destinations]: 2000</div>
			<div class="h6"><a id="561dd323e0ff85de5892770925332183"></a>(2) When [Set the number of destinations that can be specified at once to 2000] is deselected:</div>
			<div class="list">If [Cover Sheet Attachment] is [None]: 500</div>
			<div class="list">If [Cover Sheet Attachment] is [Different Sheet to Each Destination]: 100</div>
			<div class="list">If [Cover Sheet Attachment] is [Same Sheet to All Destinations]: 500</div>
			<div class="h6"><a id="9544a13f1a7161817483d4f6a22fbab3"></a>NOTE</div>
			<div class="list">In the case of groups, the above number of destinations is the number of personal destinations registered in the group.</div>
			<div class="list">The specified number of destinations (among the above) is sent separated into multiple jobs. Consequently, in the job printing log list etc., they may be displayed as separate fax transmission files.</div>
			<div class="list">There is a limit to the number of fax job destinations that can be retained in the device. In some printer models, after a fax job is sent, if the number of destinations exceeds the limit, the last job(s) sent may be deleted. If destinations exceeding the limit of the group are registered, be careful that the fax is not sent continuously to multiple group destinations.</div>
			<div class="h2"><a id="70e4d832386bc9d8389ca15bbf0f3729"></a>Cautions, Limitations and Restrictions When Installing</div>
			<div class="list">If you change the user privileges of the computer you are using and run the installer, the installation may not be performed correctly. In this case, log in as an Administrator, and then retry the installation.</div>
			<div class="list">If a message prompting you to restart your computer is displayed when using the installer, make sure to restart your computer. If you do not restart your computer, existing drivers may not operate correctly.</div>
			<div class="list">The driver may not operate correctly unless the correct region is set before installing the driver. The region can be set in either of the following locations.</div>
			<div class="dash">[Settings] &gt; [Time &amp; language] &gt; [Language &amp; region] &gt; [Region] (or [Time &amp; Language] &gt; [Region]/[Region &amp; language]) in the Start menu</div>
			<div class="dash">[Control Panel] &gt; [Region] (or [Region and Language]) in Windows</div>
			<div class="list">When installing a driver on a server computer with an SMB (NetBIOS network) printer used as a shared device specified, use the Add Printer Wizard to install it as a network printer.</div>
			<div class="list">If you are using the printer auto-creation mechanism in a Citrix XenApp environment, you may not be able to correctly install this driver using the installer. If so, restart the XenApp Server computer and check the printer list of Windows. If the printer is not displayed, re-install the driver in the XenApp Server computer with the Add Printer Wizard.</div>
			<div class="text_level2">Then, before starting the installer to install this driver, disconnect all client printers from all the ICA sessions by using the ICA Client Printer Configuration utility. After installing the driver, restart the ICA Client Printer Configuration utility and reconnect the printers.</div>
			<div class="list">For your Windows Server operation system installed with Server Core option, the following limitations exist on using this driver.</div>
			<div class="dash">You cannot install the driver with the installer. Use the installation options of Windows.</div>
			<div class="dash">Some fax options are not available under local environment or Windows Remote Desktop environment.</div>
			<div class="list">Only devices supported by version 9.00 or earlier of the fax driver enable this driver to be installed via USB.</div>
			<div class="list">This driver can coexist with version 9.xx or earlier of the fax driver. However, this driver cannot be installed by updating version 9.xx or earlier of the fax driver.</div>
			<div class="list">If SNMP is not set at the device, you may not be able to install the driver using [Standard].</div>
			<div class="list">Depending on the device name set from the device itself, the name may not be displayed correctly when it is searched during [Standard] installation.</div>
			<div class="h2"><a id="01c23a0d46d9aa6863ccd11d44e13ced"></a>Cautions, Limitations and Restrictions When Fax Sending</div>
			<div class="list">If you send using a paper size other than A4, depending on the application, you might not be able to send using the specified paper size. If this happens, reduce the magnification of the original data, specify A4, and resend the fax.</div>
			<div class="list">Depending on the application, if the number of destinations in the address book list is large, it might not operate correctly.</div>
			<div class="list">If double quotation marks or CSV separators are included in any of the items (such as name and fax numbers) stored in a CSV file, the addresses stored in the file may not be imported to the address book correctly.</div>
			<div class="list">If double quotation marks are included in any of the items (such as names and fax numbers) stored in an ABK file (*.abk), the addresses stored in the file may not be imported to the address book correctly.</div>
			<div class="list">Do not specify more than one for the copies option in the application since the fax may be sent more than once in some applications when the copies option is specified in the application.</div>
			<div class="list">In a 64-bit environment, the address book cannot be used with certain applications. If you are using an application that cannot utilize the address book, convert the address book to a CSV file, then import the CSV file into the driver as an address book.</div>
			<div class="list">The password set in [Special] sheet &gt; [Security Settings] &gt; [Protect with Password when Exporting Address List] is required to export the address list. If you do not know the password, it is necessary to create the address list again in order to export it. You can still perform operations other than exporting (browsing, adding, editing, deleting, etc.) without the password.</div>
			<div class="list">If you are using the printer auto-creation mechanism in a Citrix XenApp environment, you may not be able to use the Department ID Management function or the Retrieve Device Information function.</div>
			<div class="text_level2">If this is the case, use the Universal Printer Driver (UPD), or select a Standard TCP/IP Port for which the IP address of a device you are actually outputting to has been set.</div>
			<div class="list">The fax send settings screen may not be displayable in a Citrix environment. If this happens, try again after performing the procedure below.</div>
			<div class="text_level2">1. Display the Windows printer properties screen from the device to use.</div>
			<div class="text_level3"><span class="bold">If displaying from [Settings] in the Start menu</span></div>
			<div class="text_level3">(1) Display [Bluetooth &amp; devices] (or [Devices]).</div>
			<div class="text_level3">(2) In [Printers &amp; scanners], display the management screen for the device to set.</div>
			<div class="text_level3">To display the management screen, click the device or click [Manage] for the corresponding device.</div>
			<div class="text_level3">(3) Click [Printer properties] for the device to set.</div>
			<div class="text_level3"><span class="bold">If displaying from [Control Panel]</span></div>
			<div class="text_level3">(1) Display [Devices and Printers].</div>
			<div class="text_level3">If the [Settings] screen is displayed, refer to the above procedure for displaying the screen from [Settings].</div>
			<div class="text_level3">(2) From the printer list, right-click the device to be set → select [Printer properties] from the displayed menu.</div>
			<div class="text_level2">2. In the printer properties screen, display the [Advanced] sheet → disable [Enable advanced printing features].</div>
			<div class="list">&quot;Mobile Address Book&quot; may be displayed in the Messaging API address book, but cannot be used. The address book contacts registered in this address book are not displayed because they do not have fax information.</div>
			<div class="list">Select [Store Sent Fax Information and Image] and the sent image will be stored only on this driver. The sent image and send results may not be the same as those on the device. To check the send results of a sent fax, check the communication logs on the device.</div>
			<div class="list">Depending on the device, jobs sent by fax from the driver may not be noted in the PS print server log. Also, for jobs sent via NetWare, the logged information may not be noted correctly.</div>
			<div class="list">The communication mode you select when using IP-Fax should match the communication environment of the device. If you do not select the appropriate communication mode, it will lead to incorrect transmissions and send errors.</div>
			<div class="list">When exporting Canon Address Book files (*.abk), you can specify the character code. When importing Canon Address Book files (*.abk), there are some printer models that cannot import a Canon Address Book file (*.abk) unless the character code of the imported file matches a character code supported by the device.</div>
			<div class="list">If you specify characters unsupported by the language used in the device name, the driver may not operate normally. You can check the language used in either of the following locations.</div>
			<div class="dash">[Settings] &gt; [Time &amp; language] &gt; [Language &amp; region] &gt; [Language] (or [Time &amp; Language] &gt; [Language]/[Region &amp; language]) in the Start menu</div>
			<div class="dash">[Control Panel] &gt; [Region and Language] in Windows</div>
			<div class="list">When sending to a device that does not support the 400 x 400 dpi resolution with [Ultrafine] set in this driver, sending cannot be performed and an error is displayed on the control panel of the device. In this case, perform sending again with a resolution supported by the device.</div>
			<div class="list">When importing an address book exported from a device, characters not supported by the driver may not be read correctly.</div>
			<div class="list">You cannot use the following address books with driver versions earlier than version 8.70:</div>
			<div class="dash">Address books that have been newly created in version 8.70 or later drivers.</div>
			<div class="dash">Address books that were created in older versions and imported into version 8.70 or later drivers.</div>
			<div class="text_level2">However, you can use address books exported to files in driver versions earlier than version 8.70.</div>
			<div class="list">Sent images and profiles created with this driver cannot be used with version 9.xx or earlier of the fax driver.</div>
			<div class="list">This driver does not support the editing of an address book on the network. Editing is possible in an environment where this driver and version 10.10 or earlier of the fax driver coexist, but the changes cannot be saved.</div>
			<div class="list">Address book files in the CSV format exported from an older version of the fax driver may not be able to be imported into version 10.20 or later of this driver, depending on the language.</div>
			<div class="text_level2">If this is the case, export them as Canon Address Book files (*.abk), then import them into this driver.</div>
			<div class="list">If you are using a device made for Korea, the USA, or Canada, if you enter more than 40 single-byte numeric characters for the fax number, an error will occur at the device and the fax will not be sent.</div>
			<div class="h2"><a id="6a6da8c9f409ef3310e7d2cc63819c3c"></a>Restrictions Regarding Device Settings</div>
			<div class="text">With this driver, if you use device-dependent functions, you must retrieve the device information in the [Device Settings] sheet &gt; [Retrieve Device Information] to set the installed options to the driver. If you cannot retrieve the device information because you are connected via USB, etc., manually set the installed options on the [Device Settings] sheet.</div>
			<div class="text">Take care that you do not set functions that the device cannot use in the driver, as this can lead to mis-transmissions and transmission errors.</div>
			<div class="dash">If you set a sender with a printer model that does not have the specify sender function, you will not be able to use that function.</div>
			<div class="dash">If you select a fax board that is not compatible with the printer model you are using, and select a line that does not match a valid line to send from, there is a possibility that the fax will be sent via a different line.</div>
			<div class="dash">If you attempt to send with settings that do not match the printer model you are using for the subaddress authentication mode, department ID management authentication mode, and IP fax communication mode, you will not be able to send.</div>
			<div class="dash">If you specify the send time with a printer model that does not have the send time function, you cannot use that function.</div>
			<div class="dash">If you specify the subaddress function with a printer model that does not have the subaddress function, you cannot use that function.</div>
			<div class="dash">If you specify the [Set the number of destinations that can be specified at once to 2000] function and attempt to send with a printer model that does not support that function, this will result in a communication error or transmission error.</div>
			<div class="dash">If you set department ID management or user authentication with a printer model that does not have the department ID management function or user authentication function, you cannot use that function.</div>
			<div class="dash">If you specify the [Use Unicode (UTF-8) for Communication with Device] function and attempt to send with a printer model that does not support Unicode (UTF-8) communication, destination information etc. will not be displayed correctly.</div>
			<hr />
			<div class="text_right">Copyright Canon Inc. 1999</div>
		</div>
		<!--CONTENT_END-->
	</body>
</html>